==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Francolin
<hw>Fran"co*lin</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.; cf. It.
<ets>francolino</ets>, Sp. <ets>francolin</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A spurred partidge of the genus
<gen>Francolinus</gen> and allied genera, of Asia and Africa. The common
species (<spn>F. vulgaris</spn>) was formerly common in southern Europe,
but is now nearly restricted to Asia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Francolite</ent>⟦br⟧
